<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burnley</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 1, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to enclose for the
                            information of his excellency, Viscount Monck, a copy of a communication
                            of the 25th ultimo from M._______, <pb facs="0160" n="86" xml:id="pg_86"/> esquire, of Cincinnati, Ohio, indicating parties who would be likely
                            to give important evidence in regard to the plots and hostile
                            expeditions in Canada against the peace of the United States.</p>
                        <p>I must request that the name of the person furnishing the information may
                            be regarded as confidential.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your
                            obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hume Burnley,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>